@ the trap guys-

Actually you are both correct and incorrect.  Both traps you described are deadfalls, but a deadfall is not so specific or limited.  A deadfall is any trap in which a weight is used, free falling or 'deadfalling' and the momentum created from the weight of the 'bear falling on spikes' or the 'big object falling' is what generates the force for the kill, whether it be impalement or simple blunt force trauma.  Additionally, the writer may not be referencing the trap at all, but suggesting that the character(s) life or lives in this story are in a state of 'deadfall', which suggests that their lives are moving quickly, inevitably and uncontrollably, probably toward some sort of dangerous event or person(s).
